As soon as you can. Thanks.

775
01:00:08,160 --> 01:00:09,720
Sammy!

776
01:00:09,720 --> 01:00:11,440
Sammy!

777
01:00:11,440 --> 01:00:13,040
You see?
Samantha!

778
01:00:13,040 --> 01:00:14,760
I told you she'd be here.

779
01:00:14,760 --> 01:00:16,591
No need to worry.
Samantha!

780
01:00:18,240 --> 01:00:20,480
Sammy.

781
01:00:20,480 --> 01:00:22,360
Samantha. Samantha.

782
01:00:22,360 --> 01:00:24,240
(PANTS)

783
01:00:24,240 --> 01:00:26,880
I'm sorry I'm late.
I need you to come over here right now.

784
01:00:26,880 --> 01:00:29,040
But, Mom...
Right now! Get over here!

785
01:00:29,040 --> 01:00:31,040
Come on. Come on.

786
01:00:31,040 --> 01:00:33,360
I want you to go and wait
with Brody's mom, OK?

787
01:00:33,360 --> 01:00:35,440
Is everything alright?
How did you get here?

788
01:00:35,440 --> 01:00:37,280
I'm not entirely sure.

789
01:00:37,280 --> 01:00:39,640
Sammy was wonderful!
I think she's gonna make...

790
01:00:39,640 --> 01:00:42,712
I want you to stay away from my family!

791
01:00:45,080 --> 01:00:46,560
But you invited me.

792
01:00:46,560 --> 01:00:48,760
I did no such thing.
At the hospital.

793
01:00:48,760 --> 01:00:50,240
What hospital?

794
01:00:50,240 --> 01:00:51,673
When you came to see me.

795
01:00:52,720 --> 01:00:54,312
CC, are you alright?

796
01:00:55,800 --> 01:00:57,392
What did you call me?

797
01:00:58,440 --> 01:00:59,873
Little CC.

798
01:01:04,040 --> 01:01:07,240
Who are you?
Oh, for heaven's sake.

799
01:01:07,240 --> 01:01:09,320
Caroline, it's me.

800
01:01:09,320 --> 01:01:10,680
Charles.

801
01:01:10,680 --> 01:01:12,955
(SIREN WAIL)

802
01:01:26,640 --> 01:01:29,438
I thought we had a rule
about not talking to strangers.

803
01:01:30,960 --> 01:01:32,600
But he knew my name.

804
01:01:32,600 --> 01:01:35,751
And he just wanted to talk to me
until you got there.

805
01:01:37,680 --> 01:01:39,193
What did he want to talk about?

806
01:01:40,240 --> 01:01:43,440
First he wanted to know family stuff.

807
01:01:43,440 --> 01:01:44,873
Yeah?

808
01:01:46,600 --> 01:01:48,720
Like what we did this summer.

809
01:01:48,720 --> 01:01:50,153
And my birthday.

810
01:01:52,240 --> 01:01:54,440
What about your birthday?

811
01:01:54,440 --> 01:01:57,034
If I liked the books he sent me.

812
01:02:00,560 --> 01:02:01,993
What else?

813
01:02:03,280 --> 01:02:06,033
Then he wanted to know
about God and stuff.

814
01:02:09,040 --> 01:02:10,473
What did you tell him?

815
01:02:12,520 --> 01:02:14,078
That I didn't believe.

816
01:02:17,000 --> 01:02:18,718
Why would you say that, honey?

817
01:02:20,680 --> 01:02:25,151
Because if God was real
he wouldn't have let Daddy die.

818
01:02:35,400 --> 01:02:37,200
You know, I think...

819
01:02:37,200 --> 01:02:41,120
...I think that God knew
how wonderful Daddy was.

820
01:02:41,120 --> 01:02:44,192
And he wanted him in heaven
to make it a better place.

821
01:02:46,800 --> 01:02:48,631
It's alright that I don't believe, Mommy.

822
01:02:50,200 --> 01:02:51,633
Why?

823
01:02:53,080 --> 01:02:55,120
Grandpa doesn't believe anymore.

824
01:02:55,120 --> 01:02:58,157
So whatever happens, I'll be with him.

825
01:03:06,360 --> 01:03:07,793
Here.

826
01:03:08,840 --> 01:03:10,273
God loves you.

827
01:03:11,320 --> 01:03:13,040
And he always will, OK?

828
01:03:13,040 --> 01:03:14,473
OK.

829
01:03:19,880 --> 01:03:21,438
What did you do to your back?

830
01:03:23,440 --> 01:03:24,920
Don't know.

831
01:03:24,920 --> 01:03:27,360
It kind of itches.
Oh.

832
01:03:27,360 --> 01:03:29,400
I'll put something on it, OK?

833
01:03:29,400 --> 01:03:30,880
He, Dad, it's me.

834
01:03:30,880 --> 01:03:33,120
Look, I think there's a connection
between Adam and his alters.

835
01:03:33,120 --> 01:03:35,520
They all seem to want to know
if you have faith.

836
01:03:35,520 --> 01:03:38,560
Adam asked you, Wes asked me,
Charles asked Sammy.

837
01:03:38,560 --> 01:03:40,800
Charles?
Well...

838
01:03:40,800 --> 01:03:44,480
Adam came to Sammy's school
pretending to be Charles.

839
01:03:44,480 --> 01:03:46,471
Caroline, Charles is dead.

840
01:03:50,320 --> 01:03:52,480
What? I... Dad, I just talked to him.

841
01:03:52,480 --> 01:03:54,960
He was sick, but he didn't... I mean...

842
01:03:54,960 --> 01:03:56,678
Dad, I'm so sorry.

843
01:03:58,040 --> 01:04:00,240
Me too.

844
01:04:00,240 --> 01:04:02,360
He always had to do everything first.

845
01:04:02,360 --> 01:04:03,918
(CRIES AND COUGHS)

846
01:04:05,360 --> 01:04:07,360
Are you alright?
Yeah.

847
01:04:07,360 --> 01:04:08,793
It's just a tickle.

848
01:04:09,920 --> 01:04:11,353
I love you, sweetheart.

849
01:04:12,480 --> 01:04:13,913
I love you too, Daddy.

850
01:04:15,200 --> 01:04:16,633
Bye-bye.

851
01:04:20,160 --> 01:04:21,673
(MOANS)

852
01:04:29,000 --> 01:04:31,468
I noticed a sketchbook in your room.

853
01:04:32,960 --> 01:04:34,473
You like to draw, huh?

854
01:04:35,520 --> 01:04:37,200
Idle hands.

855
01:04:37,200 --> 01:04:40,480
Moses drowning in an unparted sea.

856
01:04:40,480 --> 01:04:41,913
Mm-hm.

857
01:04:48,720 --> 01:04:50,676
(INDISTINCT MUFFLED NOISE)

858
01:05:03,320 --> 01:05:05,038
(MYSTERIOUS GROWL)

859
01:05:23,320 --> 01:05:25,120
So, I'm seeing this, right?

860
01:05:25,120 --> 01:05:28,240
The shadow's moving. It looks like
there's somebody else there, right?

861
01:05:28,240 --> 01:05:30,080
Yeah, but...
But...

862
01:05:30,080 --> 01:05:31,560
...you know.
But... But what?

863
01:05:31,560 --> 01:05:33,200
Cara, this is... Come on, this is Dad.

864
01:05:33,200 --> 01:05:35,240
He's doing what he always does.
He's messing with you.

865
01:05:35,240 --> 01:05:37,231
Can you just find out what it is?

866
01:05:38,520 --> 01:05:39,953
Yeah, sure.

867
01:05:43,600 --> 01:05:45,320
So, uh...

868
01:05:45,320 --> 01:05:46,753
What's the deal?

869
01:05:49,600 --> 01:05:52,600
The deal, Mr Saber,
is a body found at your house.

870
01:05:52,600 --> 01:05:54,520
Excuse me?

871
01:05:54,520 --> 01:05:58,149
Male. Approximately 30-50 years of age.

872
01:06:01,520 --> 01:06:03,078
You know him?

873
01:06:04,720 --> 01:06:06,153
OK.

874
01:06:07,720 --> 01:06:09,711
Are you a religious man, Mr Saber?

875
01:06:11,280 --> 01:06:15,040
I only ask as this cross
was etched into the victim's back.

876
01:06:15,040 --> 01:06:16,920
(SNIFFS)

877
01:06:16,920 --> 01:06:18,353
Do you recognise this?

878
01:06:19,640 --> 01:06:23,474
Maybe it was burnt
or carved in, we're not sure yet.

879
01:06:26,960 --> 01:06:28,720
(MYSTERIOUS BREATHING)

880
01:06:28,720 --> 01:06:30,240
Does this mean anything to you?

881
01:06:30,240 --> 01:06:31,800
No.

882
01:06:31,800 --> 01:06:34,519
Adam, do you recognise any of these?

883
01:06:37,680 --> 01:06:39,800
Do you recognise them?

884
01:06:39,800 --> 01:06:41,640
Does this cross mean anything to you?

885
01:06:41,640 --> 01:06:45,240
(RETCHES)
Do you recognise any of these?

886
01:06:45,240 --> 01:06:46,240
(SCREAMS)

887
01:06:46,240 --> 01:06:48,360
I said, "I don't recognise them!"
Are you deaf?!

888
01:06:48,360 --> 01:06:51,160
OK. Excuse me. Excuse me, Detective.

889
01:06:51,160 --> 01:06:52,878
Can I speak to you for a second?

890
01:06:58,800 --> 01:07:01,394
Don't push him on this right now.
You 're not gonna get anywhere.

891
01:07:02,440 --> 01:07:04,760
And I... I think I can help you
with that cross.

892
01:07:04,760 --> 01:07:06,240
I've seen it somewhere before.

893
01:07:06,240 --> 01:07:07,912
Yeah.

894
01:07:13,520 --> 01:07:15,600
CARA: I saw markings like this in town.

895
01:07:15,600 --> 01:07:17,955
I'm sorry. I didn't know who else to ask.

896
01:07:23,160 --> 01:07:25,151
Dr Jessup, why are you here?

897
01:07:27,560 --> 01:07:29,994
Your textbooks have failed you,
isn't that right?

898
01:07:31,040 --> 01:07:32,360
Yes.

899
01:07:32,360 --> 01:07:33,920
So listen.

900
01:07:33,920 --> 01:07:37,515
That's why God gave us two ears
but one mouth.

901
01:07:39,400 --> 01:07:43,520
There's the Devil's magic in these hills,

902
01:07:43,520 --> 01:07:46,160
that some may try to tend an ailing child

903
01:07:46,160 --> 01:07:50,400
or take revenge for a terrible wrongdoing.

904
01:07:50,400 --> 01:07:52,520
Remember this.

905
01:07:52,520 --> 01:07:57,071
Your books may have failed you,
but your God has not.

906
01:07:58,640 --> 01:08:03,350
Follow on where the road ends
to the very top of the valley.

907
01:08:04,880 --> 01:08:08,589
You 'll see a Holler there.
Ask for the Granny.

908
01:08:11,360 --> 01:08:13,920
(TENSE MUSIC)

909
01:08:41,800 --> 01:08:43,756
Excuse me?

910
01:08:46,200 --> 01:08:48,111
I... I'm looking for the Granny.

911
01:08:59,400 --> 01:09:02,870
It's important that I find her.

912
01:09:21,360 --> 01:09:25,240
I need... I need to...
I need to find out what this is.

913
01:09:25,240 --> 01:09:27,640
I-I think it's some kind of a cross.

914
01:09:27,640 --> 01:09:30,632
Do you know what it is?

915
01:09:32,160 --> 01:09:33,718
Do you... Do you know?

916
01:09:39,840 --> 01:09:42,070
OLD WOMAN: Let me see.

917
01:09:55,600 --> 01:09:58,592
It's no cross.

918
01:10:04,240 --> 01:10:06,754
How are you doing that?

919
01:10:08,640 --> 01:10:12,480
With better eyes than yours.

920
01:10:12,480 --> 01:10:15,360
Can you tell me what it means?

921
01:10:15,360 --> 01:10:18,830
You won't believe. Child!

922
01:10:47,840 --> 01:10:51,549
(ENGINE REVS)
(MAN SCREAMS)

923
01:11:04,160 --> 01:11:05,640
What the hell is that?

924
01:11:05,640 --> 01:11:08,598
(DRUMMING)

925
01:11:15,200 --> 01:11:17,360
Want a soda?
Mm-mm.

926
01:11:17,360 --> 01:11:19,510
You sure?
Mm-hm.

927
01:11:30,840 --> 01:11:33,513
(TENSE MUSIC)

928
01:11:51,480 --> 01:11:55,320
No way. No freaking way.

929
01:11:55,320 --> 01:11:59,000
Ow! What are you doing?

930
01:11:59,000 --> 01:12:01,120
Sorry, pal.

931
01:12:01,120 --> 01:12:02,840
I need to try something.

932
01:12:02,840 --> 01:12:04,920
Uncle Stephen.

933
01:12:04,920 --> 01:12:07,309
What are you doing?
I gotta check something.

934
01:12:39,280 --> 01:12:41,510
(MUSIC INTENSIFIES)

935
01:12:52,320 --> 01:12:54,640
(MAN SCREAMS)

936
01:12:54,640 --> 01:12:55,595
Arggh!

937
01:12:57,520 --> 01:12:59,795
(CHANTS FAINTLY)

938
01:13:02,040 --> 01:13:05,800
(MAN MOANS)

939
01:13:05,800 --> 01:13:07,640
Hold him down. Hold him down!

940
01:13:07,640 --> 01:13:08,993
Keep still!

941
01:13:12,560 --> 01:13:14,240
(GASPS)

942
01:13:14,240 --> 01:13:15,958
(SUCKS AIR)

943
01:13:22,840 --> 01:13:25,877
(BLOWS AIR)

944
01:14:10,280 --> 01:14:13,317
(S SUCKS AIR)

945
01:14:15,880 --> 01:14:18,314
(BLOWS AIR)

946
01:14:23,160 --> 01:14:24,673
(GASPS)

947
01:14:26,320 --> 01:14:28,800
He'll be fine.

948
01:14:28,800 --> 01:14:31,758
(MAN MOANS)

949
01:14:35,680 --> 01:14:39,229
Now will you believe?

950
01:14:47,800 --> 01:14:50,678
It's the writing of the mountains.

951
01:14:53,640 --> 01:14:57,952
This... is shelter.

952
01:15:12,280 --> 01:15:15,200
(SIGHS)

953
01:15:15,200 --> 01:15:17,634
(MOBILE PHONE BEEPS)

954
01:15:20,800 --> 01:15:23,360
WOMAN ON VOICEMAIL:
You have two new messages.

955
01:15:23,360 --> 01:15:26,800
DETECTIVE DANTON: Dr Jessup,
this is Detective Danton.

956
01:15:26,800 --> 01:15:29,560
Just wanted to let you know
there wasn't enough to hold Adam Saber

957
01:15:29,560 --> 01:15:31,760
but we released him
into your father's care.

958
01:15:31,760 --> 01:15:34,320
Any luck with that cross? Call me.

959
01:15:34,320 --> 01:15:36,800
WOMAN: Next message.

960
01:15:36,800 --> 01:15:39,400
STEPHEN: Jesus, Carrie,
where the hell are you?

961
01:15:39,400 --> 01:15:42,840
OK, the darkness on the video,
the thing that moves...

962
01:15:42,840 --> 01:15:45,560
...it's a sound wave.

963
01:15:45,560 --> 01:15:47,040
It's a voice.

964
01:15:47,040 --> 01:15:49,440
Carrie, it's a fricking voice. Listen.

965
01:15:49,440 --> 01:15:50,919
(DEEP VOICE WHISPERS)
Reverend Christian Moore...

966
01:15:54,760 --> 01:15:57,991
...shelter now the faithless!

967
01:16:01,040 --> 01:16:02,760
Hear that?

968
01:16:02,760 --> 01:16:04,876
(DIAL TONE BEEPS)

969
01:16:06,160 --> 01:16:08,960
(PHONE BEEPS AND RINGS)

970
01:16:08,960 --> 01:16:11,160
STEPHEN: Cara.
What was that?

971
01:16:11,160 --> 01:16:17,480
Uh, I have no idea. But I do know
who Christian Moore is. Or was.

972
01:16:17,480 --> 01:16:23,240
He was born in Burlington,
Alabama, in 1889.

973
01:16:23,240 --> 01:16:25,360
He's one of those good ol' boys,

974
01:16:25,360 --> 01:16:26,840
southern faith healers.

975
01:16:26,840 --> 01:16:31,800
He died in... 1918.
That's all the info I got.

976
01:16:31,800 --> 01:16:33,480
However, listen to this. OK.

977
01:16:33,480 --> 01:16:38,120
There's some sort of historical society
in Milling Junction.

978
01:16:38,120 --> 01:16:40,200
Now, there's a guy there
by the name of Monty.

979
01:16:40,200 --> 01:16:41,960
He has all this information on him.

980
01:16:41,960 --> 01:16:45,240
OK, I'm-I'm... I'm about 50 miles
from Milling Junction now.

981
01:16:45,240 --> 01:16:46,880
You can be there in an hour. Go.

982
01:16:46,880 --> 01:16:49,838
(TENSE MUSIC)

983
01:16:54,960 --> 01:16:56,393
(COUGHS)

984
01:16:57,600 --> 01:17:01,520
You alright?
My throat scratches.

985
01:17:01,520 --> 01:17:04,440
Let me see what I got.
No cough medicines.

986
01:17:04,440 --> 01:17:06,760
Mom says it's not good for you.

987
01:17:06,760 --> 01:17:10,240
Seriously?
Honey works though.

988
01:17:10,240 --> 01:17:11,878
Yeah? OK.

989
01:17:15,800 --> 01:17:18,758
(MUSIC INTENSIFIES)

990
01:17:24,440 --> 01:17:27,080
Uncle Stephen.
Yeah?

991
01:17:27,080 --> 01:17:30,629
I think there's something on my back.

992
01:17:35,000 --> 01:17:38,720
MAN: Well, my late father
made these films

993
01:17:38,720 --> 01:17:41,075
right after the Great War.

994
01:17:43,160 --> 01:17:44,593
(CHUCKLES)

995
01:17:49,800 --> 01:17:53,040
1918.

996
01:17:53,040 --> 01:17:54,960
That's when it came.

997
01:17:54,960 --> 01:17:58,635
The influenza epidemic.

998
01:18:01,320 --> 01:18:03,840
And that's when we met him.

999
01:18:03,840 --> 01:18:06,560
The Reverend Christian Moore.

1000
01:18:06,560 --> 01:18:09,760
He was a self-proclaimed faith healer

1001
01:18:09,760 --> 01:18:13,000
and he told the Holler folks that

1002
01:18:13,000 --> 01:18:15,160
they didn't need their voodoo medicine.

1003
01:18:15,160 --> 01:18:18,400
Just faith in the Lord.

1004
01:18:18,400 --> 01:18:20,960
And he had a good number of Holler folk

1005
01:18:20,960 --> 01:18:24,032
turn their backs on the Granny.

1006
01:18:26,600 --> 01:18:31,640
You see, he used, as an example,
his own two children.

1007
01:18:31,640 --> 01:18:36,040
They were full of health
and apparently immune

1008
01:18:36,040 --> 01:18:38,720
to the ravages of the disease.

1009
01:18:38,720 --> 01:18:45,160
And they were strange children,
as I remember. Quiet.

1010
01:18:45,160 --> 01:18:48,550
Turns out that their silence
was for a good reason.

1011
01:18:50,160 --> 01:18:53,080
The Reverend had lost his faith

1012
01:18:53,080 --> 01:18:58,760
and he had had his own kin inoculated
against the disease,

1013
01:18:58,760 --> 01:19:01,200
leaving the others to die.

1014
01:19:01,200 --> 01:19:02,838
CARA: That's awful.

1015
01:19:07,200 --> 01:19:10,880
And that's why the Holler folk
did what they did.

1016
01:19:10,880 --> 01:19:13,155
What was that?

1017
01:19:15,040 --> 01:19:20,840
My father was filming as usual
and I accompanied him.

1018
01:19:20,840 --> 01:19:23,798
(MUSIC INTENSIFIES)

1019
01:19:29,080 --> 01:19:33,312
And that's when I found them -
the Reverend's children.

1020
01:19:50,280 --> 01:19:53,158
(TENSE MUSIC)

1021
01:19:54,440 --> 01:19:57,637
They dragged the Reverend
to the Granny.

1022
01:20:03,840 --> 01:20:08,960
And she handed down
her own form of mountain justice

1023
01:20:08,960 --> 01:20:11,872
for his faithless ways.

1024
01:20:14,080 --> 01:20:15,080
(MAN YELLS)

1025
01:20:15,080 --> 01:20:18,709
And I can't really tell you
what happened...

1026
01:20:23,280 --> 01:20:26,750
(SUCKS AIR)

1027
01:20:29,120 --> 01:20:30,997
...but to a child of eight...

1028
01:20:33,560 --> 01:20:36,800
...it sure as hell looked like that old hag

1029
01:20:36,800 --> 01:20:40,236
had sucked out Christian Moore's soul...

1030
01:20:42,560 --> 01:20:43,629
(BLOWS AIR)

1031
01:20:47,760 --> 01:20:54,840
...and stuffed his gullet with dirt
so that it couldn't get back in.

1032
01:20:54,840 --> 01:21:00,198
And then she said something
that I... I'll never forget.

1033
01:21:03,000 --> 01:21:07,400
Reverend Christian Moore,

1034
01:21:07,400 --> 01:21:13,794
shelter now the faithless.

1035
